President Biden delivered a speech on gun violence prevention in which he thanked healthcare professionals and individuals affected by gun violence for their courage and advocacy. He also acknowledged the efforts of Vice President Harris, members of the Cabinet, senators, and members of Congress who worked on gun legislation. The President emphasized the need for action to protect innocent lives and fulfill constitutional rights. He highlighted key provisions of the legislation, including crisis intervention and red-flag laws, enhanced background checks, closing the "boyfriend loophole," and addressing gun trafficking. The President called for a ban on assault weapons, high-capacity magazines, and the implementation of safe storage laws. He stressed the importance of expanding background checks and the responsibility of gun owners to secure their firearms. The President concluded by urging Americans to work together to ensure the safety of families, children, and fellow citizens.